svg.title: Clouds of the genera Stratocumulus, Stratus, Cumulus and Cumulonimbus: Stratus nebulosus or Stratus fractus other 6 than of bad weather,* or both
svg.desc: WMO international weather symbol: Clouds of the genera Stratocumulus, Stratus, Cumulus and Cumulonimbus: Stratus in a more or less continuous sheet or layer, or in ragged shreds, or both, but no Stratus fractus of bad weather* “Bad weather” denotes the conditions which generally exist during precipitation and a short time before and after
